.TH DEMAKE 1 "" "" "hardware\-compliant retro art & code from any image"
.SH NAME
demake \- hardware\-compliant retro art & code from any image
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdemake\fR \fIcommand\fR [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIinput\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
demake converts arbitrary images into hardware\-compliant art and code for retro consoles.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBprep\fR
Convert any image into a hardware\-compliant image for a console
.TP
\fBgen\fR
Convert an image into console data/code (bin/asm/c)
.TP
\fBconsoles\fR
List supported consoles and their constraints
.TP
\fBinspect\fR
Analyze an image: is it compliant, for which consoles, and why not
.TP
\fBcompletion\fR
Emit shell completion (bash/zsh/fish) (planned)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show help and exit.
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
Success.
.TP
\fB1\fR
A conversion ran but failed.
.TP
\fB2\fR
Wrong flags or bad command line.
.TP
\fB65\fR
Input data was malformed (EX_DATAERR).
.TP
\fB66\fR
A required input was missing (EX_NOINPUT).
.TP
\fB69\fR
A requested feature is not available yet.
.TP
\fB70\fR
An internal invariant broke (EX_SOFTWARE).
.TP
\fB73\fR
The output could not be created (EX_CANTCREAT).
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdemake-prep\fR(1), \fBdemake-gen\fR(1), \fBdemake-consoles\fR(1), \fBdemake-inspect\fR(1)
